OL,3,CMore difficult decisions ahead for the
OL,4,CBBC
OL,6,FBeware those who hide behind anodyne
OL,7,Farguments about helping hard-pressed
OL,8,Ffamily budgets. This is the government
OL,9,Fwhich abolished free TV licences for
OL,10,Fthe over-75s.
OL,12,FFreelancers in the TV industry have
OL,13,Fsuffered from a commissioning downturn
OL,14,F` a further squeeze on the BBC will
OL,15,Fonly make things worse.
OL,17,FMore importantly for the public, it is
OL,18,Fbound to lead to fewer programmes of
OL,19,Fquality and ambition.
OL,21,FAnd yet on this day of bad news for
OL,22,Fthe BBC came a little light.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/7
